title: Field hockey rankings for Oct. 22, 2015
text:
By Tom Hinkel | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 22, 2015 7:00 AM View/Post Comments 
It was an interesting week resulting in numerous changes among the top six spots. Moravian Academy dropped its first game of the season with a 3-2 loss to a very good Whitehall team on the Zephyrs' turf field. Moravian led 2-0 at halftime before the Zephyrs ran off three unanswered goals in the final 30 minutes. 
Warren Hills and Voorhees played an exciting Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex semifinal game on Saturday morning. Warren Hills prevailed 2-1, eventually winning on penalty strokes after two scoreless overtime periods. The Blue Streaks play Hunterdon Central for the H/W/S title on Saturday at Hackettstown . 
Southern Lehigh played Moravian Academy for the Colonial League title on Wednesday night. Emmaus and Stroudsburg meet for the Eastern Pennsylvania Conference championship at 6:30 tonight at Whitehall. 
Check out the full rankings by scrolling through the gallery atop this post.
